---
// about.astro — About Crestmore Research
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Crestmore Research | Independent Market Intelligence"
  description="Crestmore Research is an independent market intelligence firm delivering rigorous, data-backed analysis across technology, cybersecurity, financial services, and enterprise software."
>
  <div class="about-page">
    <!-- Page header -->
    <div class="about-page__hero">
      <h1 class="about-page__title">About Crestmore Research</h1>
      <div class="about-page__lead">
        <p>
          Crestmore Research is an independent market intelligence firm committed to delivering
          rigorous, unbiased analysis across key industry verticals. We have no affiliations with
          the vendors, platforms, or products we evaluate — our revenue comes from readers who
          value accurate, trustworthy research, not from sponsorships or paid placements.
        </p>
        <p>
          Founded with a single mandate — honest research — our team of senior analysts
          applies structured evaluation frameworks, primary data, and direct product testing to
          produce reports that cut through marketing noise. Whether you are a business leader,
          procurement professional, or informed consumer, our work gives you the intelligence you
          need to make confident decisions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Methodology -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 class="about-section__title">Our Methodology</h2>
      <div class="about-section__body">
        <p>
          Every research report published by Crestmore Research follows a standardized evaluation
          protocol designed to minimize bias and maximize analytical depth. Our process consists
          of four stages:
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Stage 1 — Market Scoping.</strong> Before testing begins, our analysts map the
          competitive landscape, identify the universe of relevant products or services, and define
          the evaluation criteria specific to the vertical. Criteria are weighted by their
          practical importance to end-users, not by what vendors prefer to be measured on.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Stage 2 — Primary Evaluation.</strong> Shortlisted products are tested directly
          by our research team. Where applicable, we conduct hands-on trials, security
          assessments, performance benchmarks, and usability reviews. All testing environments
          are controlled and documented.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Stage 3 — Comparative Scoring.</strong> Products are scored against each
          evaluation criterion using a weighted rubric. Scores are reviewed by a second analyst
          for calibration before publication. Pricing and licensing terms are verified at the
          time of publication.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Stage 4 — Editorial Review.</strong> All reports undergo a final editorial pass
          for accuracy, clarity, and completeness. Research is updated on a rolling basis
          as products change, pricing shifts, or new market entrants emerge.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Research Verticals -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 class="about-section__title">Research Verticals</h2>
      <div class="about-section__body">
        <p>
          Crestmore Research covers a focused set of market verticals where rigorous independent
          analysis is most valuable to decision-makers:
        </p>
        <div class="verticals-grid">
          <div class="vertical-item">Cybersecurity &amp; Identity</div>
          <div class="vertical-item">Enterprise Software &amp; SaaS</div>
          <div class="vertical-item">Cloud Infrastructure &amp; DevOps</div>
          <div class="vertical-item">Network &amp; Endpoint Security</div>
          <div class="vertical-item">Privacy &amp; Compliance Technology</div>
          <div class="vertical-item">Productivity &amp; Collaboration Tools</div>
          <div class="vertical-item">Financial Services Technology</div>
          <div class="vertical-item">Consumer Technology &amp; Hardware</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Editorial Standards -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 class="about-section__title">Editorial Independence</h2>
      <div class="about-section__body">
        <p>
          Crestmore Research maintains a strict separation between editorial and commercial
          operations. Vendors and service providers have no input into our scoring methodology,
          evaluation criteria, or editorial conclusions. We do not accept payment for favorable
          coverage, sponsored placements, or review manipulation of any kind.
        </p>
        <p>
          When a research report contains affiliate links, this is disclosed prominently at the
          top of the article. Affiliate relationships never influence our rankings, scoring, or
          recommendations. Our top-ranked products are determined entirely by research findings,
          regardless of whether an affiliate relationship exists.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
